# Internal SMC Readme: Unraid Deployment Guide (Start to Finish)

This guide is for an IT professional deploying Workload Tracker for the first time with limited Unraid and Docker experience.

Scope:
- Install and initialize Unraid.
- Prepare Unraid for Docker and Compose workflows.
- Clone and configure this repository.
- Deploy the stack via Compose Manager using `docker-compose.unraid.yml` as the base configuration.
- Configure SWAG reverse proxy with TLS.
- Configure router port forwarding.

Assumed target URL:
- `https://smc-projects.com`
- `https://www.smc-projects.com`

---

## 1. Architecture Overview

Workload Tracker runs as multiple containers:
- `frontend` (web UI) on host port `3000`
- `backend` (API) on host port `8000`
- `db` (PostgreSQL)
- `redis`
- `worker`, `worker_db`, `worker_beat`

On Unraid, public traffic should go through SWAG:
- `/` -> `frontend:3000`
- `/api` -> `backend:8000`

Do not expose `3000` and `8000` directly to the internet.

