## 5. Deploy with Compose Manager

### 5.1 Create stack in Compose Manager
1. Open `Docker` -> `Compose`.
2. Click `Add Stack`.
3. Stack name: `workload-tracker`.
4. Save/create the stack.

### 5.2 Load the project compose file
Use one of these methods:

Method A (recommended for first setup):
1. In terminal, copy the repo compose file into the stack project folder:
```bash
cp /mnt/user/appdata/workload-tracker/docker-compose.unraid.yml \
  /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/docker-compose.yml
```
2. In Compose Manager, click `Edit Stack` and confirm the **Compose File** tab contains the expected services.

Method B (editor paste):
1. Open `/mnt/user/appdata/workload-tracker/docker-compose.unraid.yml`.
2. Paste contents into the stack **Compose File** tab.
3. Save.

### 5.3 Create `.env` inside Compose Manager (plugin-managed)
1. In `Edit Stack`, open the **Env** tab.
2. Paste the variables from:
   `/mnt/user/appdata/workload-tracker/unraid/.env.unraid.example`
3. Replace all placeholder values (`CHANGE_ME_*`, email credentials, domain values).
4. Save.

Important:
- Compose Manager writes this to the stack project env file automatically.
- Default path is:
  `/boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/.env`
- If you set a custom env path in the stack **Settings** tab, use that path consistently.

### 5.4 Required env values to verify
At minimum confirm these are set correctly:
- `SECRET_KEY`
- `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`
- `REDIS_PASSWORD`
- `RESTORE_JOB_TOKEN_SECRET`
- `ALLOWED_HOSTS=smc-projects.com,www.smc-projects.com`
- `CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS=https://smc-projects.com,https://www.smc-projects.com`
- `COOKIE_REFRESH_AUTH=true`
- `SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=true`
- `FRONTEND_API_URL=/api`
- `FRONTEND_COOKIE_REFRESH_AUTH=true`

### 5.5 Start the stack
In Compose Manager:
- Click `Compose Up` on the `workload-tracker` stack.

### 5.6 CLI equivalent (optional validation)

```bash
docker compose \
  -f /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/docker-compose.yml \
  --env-file /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/.env \
  up -d --build
```

### 5.7 Verify local service health

```bash
docker compose -f /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/docker-compose.yml ps
docker compose -f /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/docker-compose.yml logs -f backend
curl -fsS http://<unraid-lan-ip>:8000/api/health/
```

---

### 5.8 Create the initial admin user
After services are healthy, create the first admin account:

```bash
docker compose \
  -f /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/docker-compose.yml \
  --env-file /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/.env \
  exec backend \
  python manage.py createsuperuser --username admin --email admin@smc-projects.com
```

You will be prompted to enter a password.

If the account already exists and you need to reset the password:

```bash
docker compose \
  -f /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/docker-compose.yml \
  --env-file /boot/config/plugins/compose.manager/projects/workload-tracker/.env \
  exec backend \
  python manage.py changepassword admin
```

## 6. Set Up SWAG Reverse Proxy

SWAG reference:
- https://docs.linuxserver.io/images/docker-swag/

### 6.1 Install SWAG container
1. In `Apps`, install `SWAG` (LinuxServer.io).
2. Configure cert provider and domain values for `smc-projects.com`.
3. Publish ports:
   - Host `80` -> Container `80`
   - Host `443` -> Container `443`
4. Start SWAG and confirm it is healthy.

### 6.2 Add proxy config file
Create this file:
- `/mnt/user/appdata/swag/nginx/site-confs/smc-projects.com.conf`

Sample config (replace `10.20.30.2` with your Unraid LAN IP):

```nginx
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    listen [::]:443 ssl;
    server_name smc-projects.com;

    include /config/nginx/ssl.conf;
    http2 on;

    client_max_body_size 0;

    location /api/ {
        include /config/nginx/proxy.conf;
        proxy_pass http://10.20.30.2:8000;
    }

    location /admin/ {
        include /config/nginx/proxy.conf;
        proxy_pass http://10.20.30.2:8000;
    }

    location ~ ^/calendar/.*\.ics$ {
        include /config/nginx/proxy.conf;
        proxy_pass http://10.20.30.2:8000;
    }

    location / {
        include /config/nginx/proxy.conf;
        proxy_pass http://10.20.30.2:3000;
    }
}

server {
    listen 80;
    listen [::]:80;
    server_name smc-projects.com www.smc-projects.com;
    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}

server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    listen [::]:443 ssl;
    server_name www.smc-projects.com;
    include /config/nginx/ssl.conf;
    http2 on;
    return 301 https://smc-projects.com$request_uri;
}
```

Apply changes by restarting SWAG.

### 6.3 SWAG validation
- Check SWAG logs for certificate and config errors.
- Open `https://smc-projects.com` and confirm frontend loads.
- Open `https://smc-projects.com/api/health/` and confirm API health.

